f multiple agent results with recommendations\n\n#### 2. **Plan Mode Enhancements**\n- Creates detailed implementation plans before writing code\n- New inline flowchart generation (Mermaid diagrams)\n- Task assignment functionality for improved team collaboration\n\n#### 3. **Background Agent**\n- Execute tasks without requiring real-time screen monitoring\n- Automatically completes code modifications, terminal commands, and dependency installation\n\n#### 4. **AI Model Improvements**\n- **Composer Model** (proprietary): 4x faster generation speed, completing most interactions within 30 seconds\n- Generation speed of 250 tokens/second (claimed 400% faster than competitors)\n- Supports voice-generated code\n- Enhanced code prediction and multi-line editing\n\n#### 5. **Core Features**\n- **Repository-level context understanding** through semantic search across files and history\n- **Tab completion** that predicts entire code blocks and cross-file changes\n- **Cmd+K inline editing** for precise refactoring\n- **Debug mode** for complex bugs and regressions\n- Local model deployment support for privacy\n- Code traceability and AI generation markers\n\n### Pricing Structure\n- **Free**: Limited credits (25 credits, lasts 2-3 days for professional developers)\n- **Pro**: ~$16/month (or $60/month according to some sources)\n- **Ultra**: ~$40/user/month for teams\n\n### Notable Limitations\n- Free version has very limited credits\n- Pro version is 60% more expensive than GitHub Copilot\n- Higher CPU usage in large projects\n- Occasional crashes during long-running agent operations\n\n---\n\n**Important Note**: Since these articles reference February 2026 and it's currently before that date, you may want to verify this information against official Cursor/Anysphere channels for the most accurate and up-to-date information about actual releases and changelogs.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
