ssion recovery** - continue work after interruption without reinitialization\n  - **Custom prompt library** - store personalized prompts\n  - **Integrated web search** - get real-time information without leaving CLI\n  - **VS Code extension** with graphical interface for better file management\n\n### 2. **August 2025 - GPT-5 Default Model**\n- Updated to use GPT-5 as the default model\n- Can be used directly with ChatGPT subscription (Plus, Pro, Team)\n- Installation: `npm install -g @openai/codex`\n- Updated terminal user interface and execution framework\n\n### 3. **Version 0.23.0 Release**\n- Added dynamic model switching in command line\n- Models available include gpt-5-high\n- Upgrade command: `npm install -g @openai/codex`\n- Use `/model` in interactive interface to select models\n\n### 4. **February 2026 Reference**\nOne result mentions a **February 2026 AI weekly report** noting:\n- OpenAI launched macOS version of Codex application\n- Released GPT-5.3 programming model\n- This was documented in an AI weekly report from February 9, 2026\n\n## API Pricing Information\n- **codex-mini-latest**: $1.50 per 1M input tokens, $6 per 1M output tokens\n- 75% instant cache discount available\n- Available on Responses API\n\n## Installation & Usage\n```bash\nnpm install -g @openai/codex\ncodex login\n```\n\n**Note**: The search results don't contain a specific, detailed changelog for February 2026. Most documented updates are from 2025. For the most current February 2026 changelog, I'd recommend checking OpenAI's official GitHub repository or documentation directly.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
