m/thread-1423753-1-1.html\"},{\"title\":\"让 Gemini 操控安卓手机,谷歌“屏幕自动化”功能细节曝光\",\"url\":\"https://mparticle.uc.cn/article_org.html?uc_param_str=frdnsnpfvecpntnwprdssskt#!wm_cid=734302812069966848!!wm_id=1d2d859a7da24a0187a2256ca80b9f80\"},{\"title\":\"谷歌“屏幕自动化”新进展：Gemini将操控安卓手机完成下单预约等任务\",\"url\":\"https://m.itbear.com.cn/html/2026-02/1129097.html\"},{\"title\":\"Google Gemini 拟推出屏幕自动化功能，可代用户下单及约车\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/a1856177893342532/\"},{\"title\":\"Google Gemini 拟推出屏幕自动化功能，可代用户下单及约车\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/w/1856177893342532/\"},{\"title\":\"谷歌测试新功能：Gemini将可自动操控安卓手机完成任务\",\"url\":\"https://www.pingwest.com/w/311278\"},{\"title\":\"谷歌测试新功能：Gemini将可自动操控安卓手机完成任务\",\"url\":\"https://m.163.com/dy/article/KKU9A4CB05566WT8.html\"},{\"title\":\"让Gemini操控安卓手机，谷歌“屏幕自动化”功能细节曝光\",\"url\":\"http://m.163.com/dy/article_v5/KKU8M3G50511B8LM.html\"},{\"title\":\"同花顺财经_让投资变得更简单\",\"url\":\"https://m.10jqka.com.cn/20260204/c674541754.html\"}]\n\nBased on my web search, here's what I found about **Google Gemini's Android automation feature** and the February 2026 news coverage:\n\n## Overview of the News\n\nIn **February 2026**, Google announced a significant new feature for Gemini AI: **\"Screen Automation\"** (codenamed \"**Bonobo**\"). This feature allows Gemini to directly control Android phones and perform tasks within apps.\n\n## Key Details from the Coverage\n\n### What the Feature Does\n- Gemini can automatically execute multi-step tasks like ordering food, booking rides (Uber), and making reservations\n- Uses screen automation technology to interact with specific apps on the device\n- Based on Android 16 QPR3 technical framework\n\n### Availability & Limitations\n- Initially available only in the **US and South Korea**\n- Limited to specific devices: **Pixel 10, Pixel 10 Pro, and Samsung Galaxy S26 series**\n- Currently supports specific apps in food, grocery, and ride-sharing categories\n- Runs in a secure virtual window with limited app access\n\n### Privacy & Safety Measures\nGoogle disclosed several important safeguards:\n- Users must explicitly authorize automation to start\n- Users can watch progress in real-time and stop operations at any time\n- Google warns users may be responsible for any mistakes Gemini makes\n- **Privacy concern**: Screen captures during interactions may be reviewed by human auditors to improve the service\n- Google explicitly advises users **NOT to** enter login credentials or payment information\n\n### Timeline\n- **February 4, 2026**: Initial reports leaked from Google App 17.4 beta\n- **February 26, 2026**: Official announcement at Samsung Galaxy S26 launch event\n\n## Search Results Note\n\nUnfortunately, my search **did not return specific discussions from Hacker News or Reddit** about this feature. The results primarily included coverage from Chinese tech news sites (IT之家, PingWest, DoNews, Sina), a DigitalTrends article, and various reposts. The search may not have indexed Hacker News threads or Reddit discussions from this February 2026 timeframe, or they may not exist in the accessible search results.\n\nWould you like me to try searching with different terms or a specific date filter to try to locate community reactions on these platforms?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
