ww.toutiao.com/article/7600947587264283155/\"},{\"title\":\"程序员的“贴心小伙伴”：Cursor vs. GitHub Copilot深度对比\",\"url\":\"https://m.toutiao.com/article/7600284307323716131/\"},{\"title\":\"代理 AI、MCP 与规约驱动开发：2025 年热门技术盘点\",\"url\":\"https://www.toutiao.com/a7589942471027638818/\"},{\"title\":\"更改GitHub Copilot 对话助手的AI 模型\",\"url\":\"https://docs.github.com/zh/enterprise-cloud@latest/copilot/how-tos/use-ai-models/change-the-chat-model\"},{\"title\":\"托管 GitHub Copilot 对话助手的模型\",\"url\":\"https://docs.github.com/zh/copilot/reference/ai-models/how-copilot-serves-ai-models\"},{\"title\":\"托管 GitHub Copilot 对话助手的模型\",\"url\":\"https://docs.github.com/zh/copilot/reference/ai-models/model-hosting\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub Copilot 下月起弃用部分模型，推荐使用替代选项\",\"url\":\"https://blog.csdn.net/2501_91868913/article/details/148856997\"}]\n\nBased on my search, I was not able to find a specific Hacker News discussion from February 2026 about GitHub Copilot model selection and coding agents. However, I found extensive information about GitHub Copilot's model selection features and coding agent capabilities from that time period. Here's what I discovered:\n\n## GitHub Copilot Model Selection (February 2026)\n\n### Available Models in Copilot\nAccording to GitHub's official documentation from February 2026, Copilot supported multiple AI models from different providers:\n\n**OpenAI Models:**\n- GPT-4.1, GPT-5 mini, GPT-5.1, GPT-5.1-Codex\n- GPT-5.1-Codex-Mini (Public preview)\n- GPT-5.1-Codex-Max, GPT-5.2, GPT-5.2-Codex\n- **GPT-5.3-Codex** (newly added in February 2026)\n\n**Anthropic Models:**\n- Claude Haiku 4.5\n- Claude Opus 4.5, **Claude Opus 4.6** (including fast mode preview)\n- Claude Sonnet 4, Claude Sonnet 4.5, **Claude Sonnet 4.6**\n\n**Google Models:**\n- Gemini 2.5 Pro\n- Gemini 3 Flash, Gemini 3 Pro, Gemini 3.1 Pro (all Public preview)\n\n**xAI Models:**\n- Grok Code Fast 1\n\n### Key February 2026 Updates\n\n1. **GPT-5.3-Codex Rollout** (announced February 10-11, 2026):\n   - 25% performance improvement for agentic coding tasks compared to GPT-5.2-Codex\n   - Optimized for complex, long-duration workflows\n   - Available for Copilot Pro, Pro+, Business, and Enterprise users\n   - Required administrators to manually enable the policy for teams\n\n2. **Model Selection in Coding Agent**:\n   - GitHub Mobile app update (February 2026) added the ability to select a model when using the Copilot Coding Agent\n   - Different models have different \"premium request multipliers\" affecting usage quotas\n\n3. **Model Retirements** (effective February 17, 2026):\n   - Claude Opus 4.1 → replaced by Claude Opus 4.6\n   - GPT-5 → replaced by GPT-5.2\n   - GPT-5-Codex → replaced by GPT-5.2-Codex\n\n### Auto Model Selection\n\nGitHub introduced auto model selection features that automatically choose the best AI model based on the coding context, available in both Copilot Chat and the Coding Agent.\n\n### Agent Mode vs. Ask Mode\n\nCopilot offered different modes:\n- **Agent Mode**: For autonomous coding tasks, refactoring, multi-step operations\n- **Ask Mode**: For queries and explanations\n- **Edit Mode**: For code modifications\n\nWould you like me to search for any specific aspects of GitHub Copilot's model selection or coding agent features from that time period?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
